Program: The Documentary
Title: Are Human Rights Really Universal?
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03s6svh
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 8 May 2016
Helena Kennedy QC explores the worldwide origins of human rights. She examines the philosophical foundations of the Universal Declaration, the founding document of all human rights discourse. Far from an exclusively 'Western' concept and long pre-dating the French and American revolutions and 'The Rights of Man' - they have been present around the whole globe and present for a very long time. Show less